#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an4.195"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.195:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.195:0.2"
msgid "20. Mahāvagga "
msgstr "20. The Great Chapter "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an4.195:0.3"
msgid "195. Vappasutta "
msgstr "195. With Vappa "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an4.195:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sakkesu viharati kapilavatthusmiṃ nigrodhārāme. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Sakyans, near Kapilavatthu in the Banyan Tree Monastery. "

msgctxt "an4.195:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho vappo sakko nigaṇṭhasāvako yenāyasmā mahāmoggallāno tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ mahāmoggallānaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho vappaṃ sakkaṃ nigaṇṭhasāvakaṃ āyasmā mahāmoggallāno etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Vappa of the Sakyans, a disciple of the Jains, went up to Venerable Mahāmoggallāna, bowed, and sat down to one side. Mahāmoggallāna said to him: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an4.195:2.1"
msgid "“Idhassa, vappa, kāyena saṃvuto vācāya saṃvuto manasā saṃvuto avijjāvirāgā vijjuppādā. "
msgstr "“Vappa, take a person who is restrained in body, speech, and mind. When ignorance fades away and knowledge arises, "

# NOTE: Note that here asava must mean something that flows in and defiles, as per the Jain understanding of asava, from which the Buddhist idea, I believe, is derived. The Jains understood asava as tiny particles, or pollutants, which invaded and darkened the naturally pure sould, or jiva.
#. VAR: assaveyyuṃ → anvāssaveyyuṃ (mr)
msgctxt "an4.195:2.2"
msgid "Passasi no tvaṃ, vappa, taṃ ṭhānaṃ yatonidānaṃ purisaṃ dukkhavedaniyā āsavā assaveyyuṃ abhisamparāyan”ti? "
msgstr "do you see any reason why defilements giving rise to painful feelings would defile that person in the next life?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.195:2.3"
msgid "“Passāmahaṃ, bhante, taṃ ṭhānaṃ. "
msgstr "“Sir, I do see such a case. "

msgctxt "an4.195:2.4"
msgid "Idhassa, bhante, pubbe pāpakammaṃ kataṃ avipakkavipākaṃ. "
msgstr "Take a person who did bad deeds in a past life. But the result of that has not yet ripened. "

msgctxt "an4.195:2.5"
msgid "Tatonidānaṃ purisaṃ dukkhavedaniyā āsavā assaveyyuṃ abhisamparāyan”ti. "
msgstr "For this reason defilements giving rise to painful feelings would defile that person in the next life.” "

msgctxt "an4.195:2.6"
msgid "Ayañceva kho pana āyasmato mahāmoggallānassa vappena sakkena nigaṇṭhasāvakena saddhiṃ antarākathā vippakatā hoti. "
msgstr "But this conversation between Mahāmoggallāna and Vappa was left unfinished. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.197, sc3
msgctxt "an4.195:3.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito yena upaṭṭhānasālā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi. Nisajja kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ mahāmoggallānaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then in the late afternoon, the Buddha came out of retreat and went to the assembly hall. He sat down on the seat spread out, and said to Mahāmoggallāna, "

#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an4.195:4.1"
msgid "“Kāya nuttha, moggallāna, etarahi kathāya sannisinnā; "
msgstr "“Moggallāna, what were you sitting talking about just now? "

msgctxt "an4.195:4.2"
msgid "kā ca pana vo antarākathā vippakatā”ti? "
msgstr "What conversation was unfinished?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.195:4.3"
msgid "“Idhāhaṃ, bhante, vappaṃ sakkaṃ nigaṇṭhasāvakaṃ etadavocaṃ: "
msgstr "Moggallāna repeated the entire conversation to the Buddha, and concluded: "

msgctxt "an4.195:4.4"
msgid "‘idhassa, vappa, kāyena saṃvuto vācāya saṃvuto manasā saṃvuto avijjāvirāgā vijjuppādā. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an4.195:4.5"
msgid "Passasi no tvaṃ, vappa, taṃ ṭhānaṃ yatonidānaṃ purisaṃ dukkhavedaniyā āsavā assaveyyuṃ abhisamparāyan’ti? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an4.195:4.6"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, bhante, vappo sakko nigaṇṭhasāvako maṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an4.195:4.7"
msgid "‘passāmahaṃ, bhante, taṃ ṭhānaṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an4.195:4.8"
msgid "Idhassa, bhante, pubbe pāpakammaṃ kataṃ avipakkavipākaṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an4.195:4.9"
msgid "Tatonidānaṃ purisaṃ dukkhavedaniyā āsavā assaveyyuṃ abhisamparāyan’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an4.195:4.10"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho no, bhante, vappena sakkena nigaṇṭhasāvakena saddhiṃ antarākathā vippakatā; atha bhagavā anuppatto”ti. "
msgstr "“This was my conversation with Vappa that was unfinished when the Buddha arrived.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an4.195:5.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā vappaṃ sakkaṃ nigaṇṭhasāvakaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then the Buddha said to Vappa, "

msgctxt "an4.195:5.2"
msgid "“sace me tvaṃ, vappa, anuññeyyañceva anujāneyyāsi, paṭikkositabbañca paṭikkoseyyāsi, yassa ca me bhāsitassa atthaṃ na jāneyyāsi mamevettha uttari paṭipuccheyyāsi: "
msgstr "“Vappa, we can discuss this. But only if you allow what should be allowed, and reject what should be rejected. And if you ask me the meaning of anything you don’t understand, saying: "

msgctxt "an4.195:5.3"
msgid "‘idaṃ, bhante, kathaṃ, imassa ko attho’ti, siyā no ettha kathāsallāpo”ti. "
msgstr "‘Sir, why is this? What’s the meaning of that?’” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.195:5.4"
msgid "“Anuññeyyañcevāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavato anujānissāmi, paṭikkositabbañca paṭikkosissāmi, yassa cāhaṃ bhagavato bhāsitassa atthaṃ na jānissāmi bhagavantaṃyevettha uttari paṭipucchissāmi: "
msgstr "“Sir, let us discuss this. I will do as you say.” "

msgctxt "an4.195:5.5"
msgid "‘idaṃ, bhante, kathaṃ, imassa ko attho’ti? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an4.195:5.6"
msgid "Hotu no ettha kathāsallāpo”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.198, sc6
msgctxt "an4.195:6.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, vappa, "
msgstr "“What do you think, Vappa? "

msgctxt "an4.195:6.2"
msgid "ye kāyasamārambhapaccayā uppajjanti āsavā vighātapariḷāhā, kāyasamārambhā paṭiviratassa evaṃsa te āsavā vighātapariḷāhā na honti. "
msgstr "There are distressing and feverish defilements that arise because of undertaking bodily activity. These don’t occur in someone who avoids such bodily activity. "

#. VAR: viññūhi → viññūhīti (bj, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "an4.195:6.3"
msgid "So navañca kammaṃ na karoti, purāṇañca kammaṃ phussa phussa byantīkaroti, sandiṭṭhikā nijjarā akālikā ehipassikā opaneyyikā paccattaṃ veditabbā viññūhi. "
msgstr "They don’t perform any new deeds, and old deeds are eliminated by experiencing their results little by little. This wearing away is visible in this very life, immediately effective, inviting inspection, relevant, so that sensible people can know it for themselves. "

msgctxt "an4.195:6.4"
msgid "Passasi no tvaṃ, vappa, taṃ ṭhānaṃ yatonidānaṃ purisaṃ dukkhavedaniyā āsavā assaveyyuṃ abhisamparāyan”ti? "
msgstr "Do you see any reason why defilements giving rise to painful feelings would defile that person in the next life?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.195:6.5"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“No, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "an4.195:7.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, vappa, "
msgstr "“What do you think, Vappa? "

msgctxt "an4.195:7.2"
msgid "ye vacīsamārambhapaccayā uppajjanti āsavā vighātapariḷāhā, vacīsamārambhā paṭiviratassa evaṃsa te āsavā vighātapariḷāhā na honti. "
msgstr "There are distressing and feverish defilements that arise because of undertaking verbal activity. These don’t occur in someone who avoids such verbal activity. "

