msgctxt "an4.195:8.5"
msgid "Passasi no tvaṃ, vappa, taṃ ṭhānaṃ yatonidānaṃ purisaṃ dukkhavedaniyā āsavā assaveyyuṃ abhisamparāyan”ti? "
msgstr "Do you see any reason why defilements giving rise to painful feelings would defile that person in the next life?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.195:8.6"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“No, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "an4.195:9.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, vappa, "
msgstr "“What do you think, Vappa? "

msgctxt "an4.195:9.2"
msgid "ye avijjāpaccayā uppajjanti āsavā vighātapariḷāhā, avijjāvirāgā vijjuppādā evaṃsa te āsavā vighātapariḷāhā na honti. "
msgstr "There are distressing and feverish defilements that arise because of ignorance. These don’t occur when ignorance fades away and knowledge arises. "

msgctxt "an4.195:9.3"
msgid "So navañca kammaṃ na karoti, purāṇañca kammaṃ phussa phussa byantīkaroti. "
msgstr "They don’t perform any new deeds, and old deeds are eliminated by experiencing their results little by little. "

msgctxt "an4.195:9.4"
msgid "Sandiṭṭhikā nijjarā akālikā ehipassikā opaneyyikā paccattaṃ veditabbā viññūhi. "
msgstr "This wearing away is visible in this very life, immediately effective, inviting inspection, relevant, so that sensible people can know it for themselves. "

msgctxt "an4.195:9.5"
msgid "Passasi no tvaṃ, vappa, taṃ ṭhānaṃ yatonidānaṃ purisaṃ dukkhavedaniyā āsavā assaveyyuṃ abhisamparāyan”ti? "
msgstr "Do you see any reason why defilements giving rise to painful feelings would defile that person in the next life?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.195:9.6"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“No, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "an4.195:10.1"
msgid "“Evaṃ sammā vimuttacittassa kho, vappa, bhikkhuno cha satatavihārā adhigatā honti. "
msgstr "“A mendicant whose mind is rightly freed like this has achieved six consistent responses. "

msgctxt "an4.195:10.2"
msgid "So cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā neva sumano hoti na dummano; upekkhako viharati sato sampajāno. "
msgstr "Seeing a sight with the eye, they’re neither happy nor sad, but remain equanimous, mindful and aware. "

msgctxt "an4.195:10.3"
msgid "Sotena saddaṃ sutvā … pe … "
msgstr "Hearing a sound with the ears … "

msgctxt "an4.195:10.4"
msgid "ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā … pe … "
msgstr "Smelling an odor with the nose … "

msgctxt "an4.195:10.5"
msgid "jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā … pe … "
msgstr "Tasting a flavor with the tongue … "

msgctxt "an4.195:10.6"
msgid "kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā … pe … "
msgstr "Feeling a touch with the body … "

msgctxt "an4.195:10.7"
msgid "manasā dhammaṃ viññāya neva sumano hoti na dummano; upekkhako viharati sato sampajāno. "
msgstr "Knowing a thought with the mind, they’re neither happy nor sad, but remain equanimous, mindful and aware. "

msgctxt "an4.195:10.8"
msgid "So kāyapariyantikaṃ vedanaṃ vediyamāno ‘kāyapariyantikaṃ vedanaṃ vediyāmī’ti pajānāti; jīvitapariyantikaṃ vedanaṃ vediyamāno ‘jīvitapariyantikaṃ vedanaṃ vediyāmī’ti pajānāti; "
msgstr "Feeling the end of the body approaching, they understand: ‘I feel the end of the body approaching.’ Feeling the end of life approaching, they understand: ‘I feel the end of life approaching.’ "

msgctxt "an4.195:10.9"
msgid "‘kāyassa bhedā uddhaṃ jīvitapariyādānā idheva sabbavedayitāni anabhinanditāni sītī bhavissantī’ti pajānāti. "
msgstr "They understand: ‘When my body breaks up and my life has come to an end, everything that’s felt, being no longer relished, will become cool right here.’ "

# NOTE: The thūṇa was a post to which animals were led for the sacrifice, something that gives it and its shadow a darker layer of meaning than just “stump”.
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.199, sc11
msgctxt "an4.195:11.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, vappa, thūṇaṃ paṭicca chāyā paññāyati. "
msgstr "Suppose there was a shadow cast by a sacrificial post. "

msgctxt "an4.195:11.2"
msgid "Atha puriso āgaccheyya kuddālapiṭakaṃ ādāya. "
msgstr "Then along comes a person with a spade and basket. "

msgctxt "an4.195:11.3"
msgid "So taṃ thūṇaṃ mūle chindeyya; "
msgstr "They cut down the sacrificial post at its base, "

msgctxt "an4.195:11.4"
msgid "mūle chinditvā palikhaṇeyya; "
msgstr "dig it up, "

#. VAR: usīranāḷimattānipi → usīranāḷamattānipi (bj) | usīranālimattānipi (pts1)
msgctxt "an4.195:11.5"
msgid "palikhaṇitvā mūlāni uddhareyya, antamaso usīranāḷimattānipi. "
msgstr "and pull it out by its roots, right down to the fibers and stems. "

msgctxt "an4.195:11.6"
msgid "So taṃ thūṇaṃ khaṇḍākhaṇḍikaṃ chindeyya. "
msgstr "Then they split it apart, "

msgctxt "an4.195:11.7"
msgid "Khaṇḍākhaṇḍikaṃ chetvā phāleyya. "
msgstr "cut up the parts, "

msgctxt "an4.195:11.8"
msgid "Phāletvā sakalikaṃ sakalikaṃ kareyya. "
msgstr "and chop them into splinters. "

msgctxt "an4.195:11.9"
msgid "Sakalikaṃ sakalikaṃ katvā vātātape visoseyya. "
msgstr "Next they dry the splinters in the wind and sun, "

msgctxt "an4.195:11.10"
msgid "Vātātape visosetvā agginā ḍaheyya. "
msgstr "burn them with fire, "

msgctxt "an4.195:11.11"
msgid "Agginā ḍahetvā masiṃ kareyya. "
msgstr "and reduce them to ashes. "

msgctxt "an4.195:11.12"
msgid "Masiṃ karitvā mahāvāte vā ophuṇeyya nadiyā vā sīghasotāya pavāheyya. "
msgstr "Then they sweep away the ashes in a strong wind, or float them away down a swift stream. "

msgctxt "an4.195:11.13"
msgid "Evaṃ hissa, vappa, yā thūṇaṃ paṭicca chāyā sā ucchinnamūlā tālāvatthukatā anabhāvaṃkatā āyatiṃ anuppādadhammā. "
msgstr "And so the shadow cast by the post is cut off at the root, made like a palm stump, obliterated, and unable to arise in the future. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "an4.195:12.1"
msgid "Evamevaṃ kho, vappa, evaṃ sammā vimuttacittassa bhikkhuno cha satatavihārā adhigatā honti. "
msgstr "In the same way, a mendicant whose mind is rightly freed like this has achieved six consistent responses. "

msgctxt "an4.195:12.2"
msgid "So cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā neva sumano hoti na dummano; upekkhako viharati sato sampajāno. "
msgstr "Seeing a sight with the eye, they’re neither happy nor sad, but remain equanimous, mindful and aware. "

msgctxt "an4.195:12.3"
msgid "Sotena saddaṃ sutvā … pe … "
msgstr "Hearing a sound with the ears … "

msgctxt "an4.195:12.4"
msgid "ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā … pe … "
msgstr "Smelling an odor with the nose … "

msgctxt "an4.195:12.5"
msgid "jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā … pe … "
msgstr "Tasting a flavor with the tongue … "

msgctxt "an4.195:12.6"
msgid "kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā … pe … "
msgstr "Feeling a touch with the body … "

msgctxt "an4.195:12.7"
msgid "manasā dhammaṃ viññāya neva sumano hoti na dummano; upekkhako viharati sato sampajāno. "
msgstr "Knowing a thought with the mind, they’re neither happy nor sad, but remain equanimous, mindful and aware. "

msgctxt "an4.195:12.8"
msgid "So kāyapariyantikaṃ vedanaṃ vediyamāno ‘kāyapariyantikaṃ vedanaṃ vediyāmī’ti pajānāti; jīvitapariyantikaṃ vedanaṃ vediyamāno ‘jīvitapariyantikaṃ vedanaṃ vediyāmī’ti pajānāti; "
msgstr "Feeling the end of the body approaching, they understand: ‘I feel the end of the body approaching.’ Feeling the end of life approaching, they understand: ‘I feel the end of life approaching.’ "

msgctxt "an4.195:12.9"
msgid "‘kāyassa bhedā uddhaṃ jīvitapariyādānā idheva sabbavedayitāni anabhinanditāni sītī bhavissantī’ti pajānāti”. "
msgstr "They understand: ‘When my body breaks up and my life has come to an end, everything that’s felt, being no longer relished, will become cool right here.’” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.200, sc13
msgctxt "an4.195:13.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, vappo sakko nigaṇṭhasāvako bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When he said this, Vappa the Sakyan, the disciple of the Jains, said to the Buddha: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.195:13.2"
msgid "“seyyathāpi, bhante, puriso udayatthiko assapaṇiyaṃ poseyya. "
msgstr "“Sir, suppose there was a man who raised commercial horses for profit. "

msgctxt "an4.195:13.3"
msgid "So udayañceva nādhigaccheyya, uttariñca kilamathassa vighātassa bhāgī assa. "
msgstr "But he never made any profit, and instead just got weary and frustrated. "

msgctxt "an4.195:13.4"
msgid "Evamevaṃ kho ahaṃ, bhante, udayatthiko bāle nigaṇṭhe payirupāsiṃ. "
msgstr "In the same way, I paid homage to those Jain fools for profit. "

msgctxt "an4.195:13.5"
msgid "Svāhaṃ udayañceva nādhigacchiṃ, uttariñca kilamathassa vighātassa bhāgī ahosiṃ. "
msgstr "But I never made any profit, and instead just got weary and frustrated. "

msgctxt "an4.195:13.6"
msgid "Esāhaṃ, bhante, ajjatagge yo me bālesu nigaṇṭhesu pasādo taṃ mahāvāte vā ophuṇāmi nadiyā vā sīghasotāya pavāhemi. "
msgstr "From this day forth, any confidence I had in those Jain fools I sweep away as in a strong wind, or float away as down a swift stream. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.195:13.7"
msgid "Abhikkantaṃ, bhante … pe … upāsakaṃ maṃ, bhante, bhagavā dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti. "
msgstr "Excellent, sir! … From this day forth, may the Buddha remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.195:13.8"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

